</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 06:35:25AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uoc'>16 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uoc'] = ['15 points', '16 points', '17 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uoc')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uoc" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>"Institutions will try to preserve the problem to which they are the solution."</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- Clay Shirky</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uoc"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uoc" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uoc')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uoc" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uoc')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uoc" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uoc?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uoc" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uoc')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uoc class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uoc" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uoa" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1uoa" class="parent"><a name="1uoa" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1uoa" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uoa" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1uoa" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/AlexMennen/">AlexMennen</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 06:06:58AM</span><span class="votes " >12 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uoa'] = ['11 points', '12 points', '13 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1uoa')">[+] (7 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1uoa" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1uoa" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/AlexMennen/">AlexMennen</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 06:06:58AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uoa'>12 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uoa'] = ['11 points', '12 points', '13 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uoa')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uoa" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>An atheist walked into a bar, but seeing no bartender he revised his initial assumption and decided he only walked into a room.</p>
</blockquote>

<p><a href="http://friendlyatheist.com/2008/02/29/complete-the-atheist-joke-1/" rel="nofollow">http://friendlyatheist.com/2008/02/29/complete-the-atheist-joke-1/</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uoa"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uoa" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uoa')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uoa" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uoa')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uoa" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uoa?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uoa" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uoa')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uoa class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uoa" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1uoa" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1uoa" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uom" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1uom" class="parent"><a name="1uom" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1uom" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uom" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1uom" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Waldheri/">Waldheri</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 08:33:47AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uom'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1uom')">[+] (6 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1uom" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1uom" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Waldheri/">Waldheri</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 08:33:47AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uom'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uom'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uom')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uom" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>My initial response was to chuckle, but when my analytical capacities kicked in a moment later I was disappointed.</p>

<p>If his initial assumptions was that he was walking into a bar, does that make him atheist in this metaphor? Substitute "walked into a bar" by "believed there is a god", the thing I assume it is a metaphor of. You will see it makes no sense.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uom"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uom" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uom')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uom" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uom')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uom" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uom?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1uom" href="#1uoa" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uom" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uom')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uom class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uom" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1uom" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1uom" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1upx" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1upx" class="parent"><a name="1upx" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1upx" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1upx" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1upx" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/AlexMennen/">AlexMennen</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 03:22:03PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1upx'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1upx')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1upx" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1upx" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/AlexMennen/">AlexMennen</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 03:22:03PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1upx'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1upx'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1upx')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1upx" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Many atheists were formerly theists.</p>

<p>Still, I suppose it might have been better as "A scientist walked into what he thought was a bar, but seeing no bartender, barstools, or drinks, he revised his initial assumption and decided he only walked into a room."</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1upx"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1upx" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1upx')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1upx" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1upx')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1upx" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1upx?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1upx" href="#1uom" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1upx" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1upx')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1upx class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1upx" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uoo" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1uoo" class="parent"><a name="1uoo" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1uoo" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uoo" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1uoo" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/roundsquare/">roundsquare</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 09:02:08AM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uoo'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1uoo')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1uoo" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1uoo" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/roundsquare/">roundsquare</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 09:02:08AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uoo'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uoo'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uoo')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uoo" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I think it makes sense, as a poke at atheists.</p>

<p>Think about it this way. You walk into a bar, and you see no bartender. In your mind, you say "anything that is a bar will have a bartender. No bar tender, not a bar." Of course, the best thing to do before revising your assumptions is to wait for a bar tender. Maybe he/she is in the bathroom.</p>

<p>Similarly, if you claim there is no evidence of god that I've seen in my lifetime, you are using the wrong measure. Why should god (if there is one) make itself obvious during the short period that is a human lifetime.</p>

<p>This is almost an "irrationality quote" instead of a rationality quote, but still enlightening.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uoo"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uoo" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uoo')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uoo" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uoo')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uoo" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uoo?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1uoo" href="#1uom" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uoo" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uoo')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uoo class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uoo" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1uoo" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1uoo" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1up9" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1up9" class="parent"><a name="1up9" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1up9" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1up9" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1up9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 12:40:27PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1up9'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1up9')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1up9" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1up9" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 12:40:27PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1up9'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1up9'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1up9')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1up9" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I was with you up until the "similarly". After that you start <a href="http://wiki.lesswrong.com/wiki/Privileging_the_hypothesis">privileging the hypothesis</a> - you <em>should</em> expect a god to make itself obvious during a human lifetime, by any description of a god ever proposed in history.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1up9"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1up9" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1up9')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1up9" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1up9')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1up9" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1up9?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1up9" href="#1uoo" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1up9" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1up9')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1up9 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1up9" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1up9" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1up9" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uw9" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_1uw9" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_1uw9" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uw9" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_1uw9" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_1uw9" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_1uw9" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_20y', ['1uw9'], 4)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(3 replies)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="e