comment('t1_1uhl')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uhl" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I'm a big fan of Ken Binmore, and this quote captures a lot of my dissatisfaction with LW's directions of inquiry. For example, it's more or less taken for granted here that future superintelligent AIs should cooperate on the Prisoner's Dilemma, so some of us set out to create a general theory of "superintelligent AIs" (including ones built by aliens, etc.) that would give us the answer we like.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uhl"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uhl" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uhl')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uhl" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uhl')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uhl" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uhl?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1uhl" href="#1ugt" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uhl" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uhl')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uhl class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uhl" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1uhl" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1uhl" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1und" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1und" class="parent"><a name="1und" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1und" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1und" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1und" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Zubon/">Zubon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 12:57:39AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1und'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1und')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1und" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1und" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Zubon/">Zubon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 April 2010 12:57:39AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1und'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1und'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1und')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1und" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Would it be correct to say you mean "should" in the wishful thinking sense of "we really want this outcome," rather than something normative or probabilistic?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1und"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1und" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1und')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1und" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1und')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1und" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1und?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1und" href="#1uhl" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1und" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1und')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1und class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1und" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1und" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1und" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1up6" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_1up6" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_1up6" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1up6" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_1up6" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_1up6" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="