<p>It sounds like the author is upset that psychologists don't believe he has a model of behavior that explains 99% of some output variable using only one input variable.  I'd have a hard time believing too.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ug6"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ug6" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ug6')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ug6" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ug6')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ug6" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1ug6?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ug6" href="#1uf5" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ug6" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ug6')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ug6 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ug6" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ud1" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ud1" class="parent"><a name="1ud1" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ud1" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ud1" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ud1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/djcb/">djcb</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 12:20:39PM</span><span class="votes " >12 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ud1'] = ['11 points', '12 points', '13 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ud1')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ud1" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ud1" href="h