 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uey')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uey" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Such sad statistical situations suggest that the marriage of science and math may be desperately in need of counseling. Perhaps it could be provided by the Rev. Thomas Bayes.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Tom Siegfried, <a href="http://www.sciencenews.org/view/feature/id/57091/title/Odds_are,_its_wrong" rel="nofollow">Odds Are, It&#39;s Wrong</a>, on the many failings of traditional statistics in modern science.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uey"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uey" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uey')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uey" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uey')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uey" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uey?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uey" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uey')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uey class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uey" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1udd" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1udd" class="parent"><a name="1udd" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1udd" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1udd" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1udd" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Tetronian/">Tetronian</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 01:56:15PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1udd'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1udd')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1udd" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1udd" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Tetronian/">Tetronian</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 01:56:15PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1udd'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1udd'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1udd')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1udd" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
