</blockquote>

<p>--Voltaire</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1udd"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1udd" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1udd')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1udd" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1udd')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1udd" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1udd?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1udd" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1udd')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1udd class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1udd" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1u9r" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1u9r" class="parent"><a name="1u9r" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1u9r" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1u9r" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1u9r" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 April 2010 11:44:06PM</span><span class="votes " >33 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1u9r'] = ['32 points', '33 points', '34 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1u9r')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1u9r" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1u9r" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 April 2010 11:44:06PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1u9r'>33 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1u9r'] = ['32 points', '33 points', '34 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1u9r')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1u9r" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>I listen to all these complaints about rudeness and intemperateness, and the opinion that I come to is that there is no polite way of asking somebody: have you considered the possibility that your entire life has been devoted to a delusion? But that’s a good question to ask. Of course we should ask that question and of course it’s going to offend people. Tough.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Daniel Dennett, <a href="http://www.philosophypress.co.uk/?p=1001" rel="nofollow">interview for TPM: The Philosopher&#39;s Magazine</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1u9r"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1u9r" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1u9r')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1u9r" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1u9r')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1u9r" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1u9r?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1u9r" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1u9r')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1u9r class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1u9r" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1u9r" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1u9r" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uxi" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1uxi" class="parent"><a name="1uxi" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1uxi" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uxi" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1uxi" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Rain/">Rain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 April 2010 05:53:47PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uxi'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1uxi')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1uxi" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1uxi" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Rain/">Rain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 April 2010 05:53:47PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uxi'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uxi'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uxi')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uxi" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>If the point is to get them to answer or reason about the topic, then I think we should reject the statement that "there is no polite way of asking." We should <em>find</em> a way of asking politely, such as teaching them to process our questions instead of answering with cached thoughts. Being offensive doesn't win.</p>

<p>I also think it's a poorly phrased question, since it's easily brushed off with "yes/no", avoiding any of the deeper implications in an apparent effort to make it catchy and instantly polarizing.</p>

<p>If the point is to upset people, to feel righteous, or to signal tribal affiliation, then go right ahead.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uxi"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uxi" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uxi')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uxi" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uxi')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uxi" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uxi?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1uxi" href="#1u9r" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uxi" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uxi')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uxi class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uxi" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1uxi" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1uxi" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uyd" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1uyd" class="parent"><a name="1uyd" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1uyd" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uyd" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1uyd" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 April 2010 07:27:47PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uyd'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1uyd')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1uyd" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1uyd" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 April 2010 07:27:47PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uyd'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uyd'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uyd')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uyd" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Being offensive doesn't win.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>This is not universally true, but I would support trying to create nonoffensive ways to deliver the message - <a href="http://gretachristina.typepad.com/greta_christinas_weblog/2007/09/good-cop-bad-co.html" rel="nofollow">the combination of direct and conciliatory methods is probably more powerful than either alone</a>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uyd"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uyd" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uyd')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uyd" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uyd')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uyd" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uyd?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1uyd" href="#1uxi" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uyd" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uyd')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uyd class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uyd" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1uyd" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1uyd" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uyg" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1uyg" class="parent"><a name="1uyg" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1uyg" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uyg" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1uyg" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Rain/">Rain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 April 2010 07:35:06PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uyg'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1uyg')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1uyg" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1uyg" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Rain/">Rain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 April 2010 07:35:06PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uyg'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uyg'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uyg')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uyg" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Yes, I considered that to be the primary statement under contention.</p>

<p>It's not a strategy I wish to use, so I decided to speak out against it even as I realize that's kind of the point, to have purists who can continue to show that there's further to go, and a spectrum of other positions to provide a more gradual path.</p>

<p>I recognize the potential usefulness of it even as I deride it; I am good cop.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uyg"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uyg" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uyg')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uyg" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uyg')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uyg" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uyg?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1uyg" href="#1uyd" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uyg" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uyg')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uyg class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uyg" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1u9s" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1u9s" class="parent"><a name="1u9s" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1u9s" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1u9s" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1u9s" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 April 2010 11:44:53PM</span><span class="votes " >26 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1u9s'] = ['25 points', '26 points', '27 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1u9s')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1u9s" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1u9s" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 April 2010 11:44:53PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1u9s'>26 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1u9s'] = ['25 points', '26 points', '27 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1u9s')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1u9s" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>My dad used to have an expression:  "Don't tell me what you value. Show me your budget, and I'll tell you what you value."</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Joe Biden, <a href="http://my.barackobama.com/page/community/post/amandascott/gG5qpz" rel="nofollow">remarks delivered in Saint Clair Shores, MI, Monday, September 15, 2008</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1u9s"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1u9s" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1u9s')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1u9s" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1u9s')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1u9s" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1u9s?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1u9s" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1u9s')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1u9s class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1u9s" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1u9s" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1u9s" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ua7" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ua7" class="parent"><a name="1ua7" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ua7" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ua7" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ua7" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Peter_de_Blanc/">Peter_de_Blanc</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 01:13:01AM</span><span class="votes " >20 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ua7'] = ['19 points', '20 points', '21 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ua7')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ua7" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ua7" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Peter_de_Blanc/">Peter_de_Blanc</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 01:13:01AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ua7'>20 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ua7'] = ['19 points', '20 points', '21 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ua7')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ua7" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Of course, to really see what someone values you'd have to see their budget profile across a wide range of wealth levels.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ua7"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ua7" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ua7')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ua7" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ua7')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ua7" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1ua7?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ua7" href="#1u9s" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ua7" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ua7')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ua7 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ua7" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ua2" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ua2" class="parent"><a name="1ua2" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ua2" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ua2" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ua2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Yvain/">Yvain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 12:46:16AM</span><span class="votes " >20 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ua2'] = ['19 points', '20 points', '21 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ua2')">[+] (52 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ua2" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ua2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Yvain/">Yvain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 12:46:16AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ua2'>20 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ua2'] = ['19 points', '20 points', '21 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ua2')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ua2" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>"Everyone thinks they've won the Magical Belief Lottery. Everyone thinks they more or less have a handle on things, that they, as opposed to the billions who disagree with them, have somehow <em>lucked</em> into the one true belief system."</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- R Scott Bakker, <em>Neuropath</em></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ua2"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ua2" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ua2')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ua2" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ua2')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ua2" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1ua2?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ua2" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ua2')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ua2 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ua2" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1ua2" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1ua2" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ua3" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ua3" class="parent"><a name="1ua3" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ua3" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ua3" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ua3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/cousin_it/">cousin_it</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 12:48:25AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ua3'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ua3')">[+] (51 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ua3" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ua3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/cousin_it/">cousin_it</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 12:48:25AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ua3'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ua3'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ua3')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ua3" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>You mean, like every Bayesian believes <em>their</em> prior is correct?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ua3"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ua3" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ua3')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ua3" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ua3')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ua3" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1ua3?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ua3" href="#1ua2" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ua3" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ua3')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ua3 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ua3" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1ua3" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1ua3" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uc2" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1uc2" class="parent"><a name="1uc2" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1uc2" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uc2" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1uc2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 08:22:25AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uc2'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1uc2')">[+] (17 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1uc2" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1uc2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 08:22:25AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uc2'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uc2'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uc2')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uc2" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Prior can't be judged. It's not assumed to be "correct". It's just <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/hk/priors_as_mathematical_objects/">the way you happen to process new info and make decisions</a>, and there is no procedure to change the way it is from inside the system.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uc2"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uc2" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uc2')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uc2" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uc2')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uc2" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uc2?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1uc2" href="#1ua3" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uc2" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uc2')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uc2 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uc2" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1uc2" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1uc2" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ucc" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ucc" class="parent"><a name="1ucc" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ucc" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ucc" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ucc" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/cousin_it/">cousin_it</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 09:54:11AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ucc'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ucc')">[+] (13 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ucc" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ucc" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/cousin_it/">cousin_it</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 09:54:11AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ucc'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ucc'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ucc')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ucc" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Locked in, huh? Then I don't want to be a Bayesian.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ucc"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ucc" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ucc')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ucc" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ucc')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ucc" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1ucc?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ucc" href="#1uc2" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ucc" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ucc')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ucc class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ucc" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1ucc" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1ucc" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ue3" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ue3" class="parent"><a name="1ue3" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ue3" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ue3" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ue3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/neq1/">neq1</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 03:45:20PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ue3'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ue3')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ue3" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ue3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/neq1/">neq1</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 03:45:20PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ue3'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ue3'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ue3')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ue3" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>If someone was locked in to a belief, then they'd use a point mass prior.  All other priors express some uncertainty.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ue3"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ue3" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ue3')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ue3" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ue3')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ue3" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1ue3?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ue3" href="#1ucc" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ue3" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ue3')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ue3 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ue3" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ucs" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ucs" class="parent"><a name="1ucs" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ucs" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ucs" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ucs" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 11:29:37AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ucs'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ucs')">[+] (11 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ucs" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ucs" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 11:29:37AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ucs'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ucs'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ucs')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ucs" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Since you are <em>already</em> locked in in some preference anyway, you should figure out how to compute within it best (build a FAI).</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ucs"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ucs" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ucs')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ucs" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ucs')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ucs" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1ucs?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ucs" href="#1ucc" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ucs" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ucs')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ucs class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ucs" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1ucs" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1ucs" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1udl" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1udl" class="parent"><a name="1udl" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1udl" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1udl" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1udl" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/cousin_it/">cousin_it</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 02:39:04PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1udl'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1udl')">[+] (10 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1udl" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1udl" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/cousin_it/">cousin_it</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 02:39:04PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1udl'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1udl'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1udl')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1udl" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>you are already locked in in some preference anyway</p>
</blockquote>

<p>What makes you say that? It's not true. My preferences have changed many times.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1udl"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1udl" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1udl')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1udl" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1udl')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1udl" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1udl?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1udl" href="#1ucs" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1udl" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1udl')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1udl class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1udl" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1udl" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1udl" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uew" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1uew" class="parent"><a name="1uew" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1uew" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uew" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1uew" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 06:06:10PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uew'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1uew')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1uew" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1uew" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 06:06:10PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uew'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uew'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uew')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uew" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Distinguish formal preference and likes. Formal preference is like prior: both current beliefs and procedure for updating the beliefs; beliefs change, but not the procedure. Likes are like beliefs: they change all the time, according to formal preference, in response to observations and reflection. Of course, we might consider jumping to a meta level, where the procedure for updating beliefs is itself subject to revision; this doesn't really change the game, you've just named some of the beliefs changing according to fixed prior "object-level priors", and named the process of revising those beliefs according to the fixed prior "process of changing object-level prior".</p>

<p>When formal preference changes, it by definition means that it changed not according to (former) formal preference, that is something undesirable happened. Humans are not able to hold their preference fixed, which means that their preferences do change, what I call "value drift".</p>

<p>You are locked in in some preference in normative sense, not factual. This means that value drift does change your preference, but it is actually desirable (for you) for your formal preference to never change.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uew"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uew" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uew')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uew" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uew')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uew" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uew?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1uew" href="#1udl" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uew" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uew')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uew class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uew" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1uew" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1uew" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uhj" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1uhj" class="parent"><a name="1uhj" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1uhj" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uhj" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1uhj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/cousin_it/">cousin_it</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 April 2010 11:31:43AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uhj'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1uhj')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1uhj" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1uhj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/cousin_it/">cousin_it</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 April 2010 11:31:43AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uhj'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uhj'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uhj')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uhj" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Formal preference is like prior: both current beliefs and procedure for updating the beliefs; beliefs change, but not the procedure.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>I object to your talking about "formal preference" without having a formal definition. Until you invent one, please let's talk about what normal humans mean by "preference" instead.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uhj"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uhj" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uhj')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uhj" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uhj')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uhj" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uhj?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1uhj" href="#1uew" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uhj" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uhj')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uhj class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uhj" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1uhj" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1uhj" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uhk" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_1uhk" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_1uhk" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uhk" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_1uhk" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_1uhk" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_1uhk" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_20y', ['1uhk'], 8)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(3 replies)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uhk"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uhk" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uel" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_1uel" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_1uel" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uel" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_1uel" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_1uel" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_1uel" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_20y', ['1uel'], 6)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(5 replies)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uel"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uel" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1us5" class="morechildren" ><div id="pre_t1_1us5" class="parent"></div><div id="entry_t1_1us5" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1us5" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'></div><div id="display_t1_1us5" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"></div><div id="body_t1_1us5" class="comment-content"><span class="morecomments"><a style="font-size: smaller; font-weight: bold" id="more_t1_1us5" href="javascript:void()" onclick="return morechildren(this, 't3_20y', ['1us5', '1uj0'], 3)">load more comments<span class="gray">&nbsp;(3 replies)</span></a></span></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1us5"></div><div class="comment-links"></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1us5" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ube" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ube" class="parent"><a name="1ube" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ube" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ube" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ube" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Liron/">Liron</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 04:27:39AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ube'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ube')">[+] (32 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ube" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ube" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Liron/">Liron</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 04:27:39AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ube'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ube'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ube')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ube" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Bayesians don't believe they lucked into their priors. They have a reflectively consistent causal explanation for their priors.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ube"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ube" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ube')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ube" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ube')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ube" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1ube?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ube" href="#1ua3" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ube" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ube')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ube class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ube" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1ube" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1ube" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ubi" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ubi" class="parent"><a name="1ubi" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ubi" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ubi" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ubi" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Unknowns/">Unknowns</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 05:19:23AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ubi'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ubi')">[+] (31 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ubi" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ubi" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Unknowns/">Unknowns</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 05:19:23AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ubi'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ubi'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ubi')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ubi" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Even if their explanation were correct, they would still have lucked into them. Others have different priors and no doubt different causes for their priors. So those Bayesians would have been lucky, in order to have the causes that would produce correct priors instead of incorrect ones.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ubi"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ubi" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ubi')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ubi" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ubi')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ubi" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1ubi?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ubi" href="#1ube" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ubi" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ubi')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ubi class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ubi" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1ubi" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1ubi" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uer" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1uer" class="parent"><a name="1uer" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1uer" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uer" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1uer" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Eliezer_Yudkowsky/">Eliezer_Yudkowsky</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 05:43:01PM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uer'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1uer')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1uer" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1uer" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Eliezer_Yudkowsky/">Eliezer_Yudkowsky</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 05:43:01PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uer'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uer'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uer')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uer" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>But that still doesn't need to be <em>luck</em>.  I got my priors offa evolution and they are capable of noticing when something works or doesn't work a hundred times in a row.  True, if I had a different prior, I wouldn't care about <em>that</em> either.  But even so, that I have this prior is not a question of <em>luck</em>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uer"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uer" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uer')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uer" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uer')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uer" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uer?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1uer" href="#1ubi" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uer" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uer')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uer class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uer" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1uer" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1uer" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uj2" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1uj2" class="parent"><a name="1uj2" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1uj2" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uj2" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1uj2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Yvain/">Yvain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 April 2010 10:30:13PM</span><span class="votes " >5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uj2'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1uj2')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1uj2" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1uj2" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Yvain/">Yvain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 April 2010 10:30:13PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uj2'>5 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uj2'] = ['4 points', '5 points', '6 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uj2')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uj2" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>It is luck in a sense - every way that your opinion differs from someone else, you believe that factors outside of your control (your intelligence, your education, et cetera) have blessed you in such a way that your mind has done better than that poor person's.</p>

<p>It's just that it's not a problem. Lottery winners got richer than everyone else by luck, but that doesn't mean they're deluded in believing that they're rich. But someone who had only weak evidence ze won the lottery should be very skeptical. The real point of this quote is that being much less wrong than average is an improbable state, and you need correspondingly strong evidence to support the possibility. I think many of the people on this site probably do have some of that evidence (things like higher than average IQ scores would be decent signs of higher than normal probability of being right) but it's still something worth worrying about.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1uj2"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1uj2" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uj2')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1uj2" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1uj2')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1uj2" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1uj2?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1uj2" href="#1uer" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1uj2" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1uj2')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1uj2 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1uj2" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1uj2" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1uj2" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ujd" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ujd" class="parent"><a name="1ujd" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ujd" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ujd" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ujd" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Eliezer_Yudkowsky/">Eliezer_Yudkowsky</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 April 2010 01:24:22AM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ujd'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ujd')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ujd" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ujd" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Eliezer_Yudkowsky/">Eliezer_Yudkowsky</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">04 April 2010 01:24:22AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ujd'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ujd'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ujd')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ujd" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I think I agree with that:  There's nothing necessarily delusive about believing you got lucky, but it should generally require (at least) an amount of evidence proportional to the amount of purported luck.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ujd"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ujd" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ujd')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ujd" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ujd')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ujd" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1ujd?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ujd" href="#1uj2" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ujd" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ujd')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ujd class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ujd" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1