 '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ubf')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ubf" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Sounds like a traditional-rationality precursor to "hypotheses are expectation-constrainers".</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ubf"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ubf" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ubf')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ubf" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ubf')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ubf" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1ubf?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ubf" href="#1u95" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ubf" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ubf')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ubf class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ubf" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1ubf" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1ubf" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1ubu" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1ubu" class="parent"><a name="1ubu" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1ubu" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1ubu" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1ubu" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 06:33:49AM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ubu'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1ubu')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1ubu" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1ubu" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 06:33:49AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1ubu'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1ubu'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1ubu')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1ubu" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>It doesn't sound like that to me. Can you elaborate?</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1ubu"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1ubu" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ubu')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1ubu" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1ubu')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1ubu" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1ubu?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1ubu" href="#1ubf" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1ubu" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1ubu')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1ubu class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1ubu" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_1ubu" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_1ubu" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1uem" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1uem" class="parent"><a name="1uem" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1uem" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1uem" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1uem" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Warrigal/">Warrigal</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 05:00:29PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uem'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_1uem')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_1uem" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_1uem" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Warrigal/">Warrigal</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 April 2010 05:00:29PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_1uem'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1uem'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1uem')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1uem" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Well, the quote could be interpreted as "Any scientific theory must ultimately produce some numbers, so that reality can be measured and we can see whether the numbers match."</p>

