a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_1vgy')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_1vgy" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>"Like any dogma, it is honored far more in the breach than in the observance."</p>
</blockquote>

<p>As is appropriate when the dogma in question is trivially observed yet distracting when breached. I would expect dogma to be encouraged with honor for observance more when the reverse is the case. For example, when a dogma pertains to a particularly noble or self sacrificial action that is far rarer than the 'null' breach.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_1vgy"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_1vgy" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1vgy')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_1vgy" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_1vgy')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_1vgy" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/20y/rationality_quotes_april_2010/1vgy?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_1vgy" href="#1v8v" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_1vgy" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_1vgy')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_1vgy class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_1vgy" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_1v7c" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_1v7c" class="parent"><a name="1v7c" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_1v7c" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_1v7c" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_1v7c" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RobinZ/">RobinZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">09 April 2010 03:16:28AM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_1v7c'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" 